@thenorthface has deflated its most famous creation, transforming the iconic Nuptse puffer into the Nuptse shirt. Stripping away the insulation but retaining much of the functionality, the summer-ready silhouette arrives in water-repellent recycled nylon with snap-button closures and the same short, wide fit that helped make the original a menswear favorite.⁠
⁠
The short-sleeve styles mirror the Nuptse’s signature two-tone color blocking, while a long-sleeve version reimagines the design in denim-look nylon. Essentially, it’s everything that makes the OG Nuptse great, just in shirt form. The catch? For now, it’s only available in Japan through Goldwin’s The North Face division.⁠

