@lelabofragrances Santal 33 is already one of the most recognizable scents in modern fragrance, lingering everywhere from artisan coffee shops to Brooklyn sidewalks. More than a decade after becoming the brand’s breakout hit, the smoky, woody bestseller remains Le Labo’s top seller and continues to expand its reach.⁠
⁠
To mark its 20th anniversary, Le Labo is introducing a Santal 33 hand care kit, pairing a scented hand soap with a matching lotion infused with the fragrance’s signature cedarwood character. The launch joins an already growing Santal universe that includes shower gel, body bar, the original Santal 26 candle, and, most recently, Le Labo’s debut incense collection featuring handmade Kyoto-crafted sticks available in Santal 26, Encens 9, and Ambroxyde 17.⁠

@obj has spent more than a decade as one of the NFL’s most extravagant dressers, and now a portion of his coveted wardrobe is headed to auction. Through Pharrell’s online auction house @joopiterofficial, OBJ is selling a selection of designer pieces, game-worn memorabilia, and rare vintage T-shirts to benefit the OBJ Foundation’s work with underserved youth.⁠
⁠
While standout lots include a Chanel Graffiti briefcase and Virgil Abloh-era Louis Vuitton outerwear, the auction’s real MVP is Beckham’s impressive stash of vintage tees. From a sun-faded 1993 Cleveland Browns shirt and Baltimore Ravens Super Bowl tees to ‘90s rap grails featuring Tupac, The Notorious B.I.G., and Snoop Dogg, the collection reflects OBJ’s taste for hard-to-find classics that vintage collectors spend years chasing.⁠

@jiyongkim_official’s next PUMA collaboration started with a piece of paper.
Since launching his label, Jiyong Kim has built an extensive archive of found garments, objects and ephemera, often using them as references for the sun-bleached treatments that have become a signature of his work. For his upcoming PUMA collaboration, arriving this November, Kim looked to aged paper stained by time, dirt, mold and decay.
The result is a print applied across the upper of the PUMA CELL GEO 1, turning years of natural deterioration into something entirely new. Swipe for a first look.

@rosalia.vt and @dior are a match made in fashion heaven—her latest tour only proves that.
From a live orchestra and ballet-inspired performances to references to iconic paintings and Elizabethan fashion trends, it's obvious Rosalía knew her history ahead of the 'Lux Tour,' and who better to bring her vision to life than jonathan.anderson? Working closely with her stylist @joecarayol and the team at Dior, they have crafted looks that capture the heart of the album beautifully. As #Rosalia gears up to bring her show to New York City, let's take a look at the process behind some of the best fashion moments from the tour so far.
📷 Courtesy of Dior

