Silver has been part of Indian culture for centuries, usually found sitting in a box or stored in the back of the cupboard. Shynora placed 925 sterling silver in couture. Drawing from India’s oldest craft traditions of filigree, nakashi, hand-strung stone work, each piece is designed for the woman who carries her silver, not stores it. The silver is BIS hallmarked and handcrafted by skilled kaarigars and is meant to be worn.
